text: Memorabilia (Latin: "things worthy of being remembered") may refer to: ;Objects preserved and collected as souvenirs * Memorabilia * Memorabilia (event), an event held twice annually in Birmingham for collectors of memorabilia ;Ancient literary works * Memorabilia (Xenophon), a collection of Socratic dialogues by Xenophon * Factorum ac dictorum memorabilium libri IX by Valerius Maximus ;Other * Memorabilia – The Singles, a compilation album by Soft Cell with Marc Almond * "Memorabilia", a 1980 song by Soft Cell * "Memorabilia" (The Flash), an episode of The Flash ==See also== * Hypomnemata (disambiguation) * *
